# Context hierarchy

1. Read [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) for stack and cross-cutting rules.
2. When editing `front/**`, read [front/sub.md](mdc:front/sub.md) — React structure for this repo only.
3. When editing `server/**`, read [server/sub.md](mdc:server/sub.md) — Express MVC for this repo only.
4. Publish HTML → React: read [front/docs/publish-to-jsx.md](mdc:front/docs/publish-to-jsx.md) and use `@html-publish-to-react`.

Do not invent a different folder layout than `sub.md` describes unless the user asks to change architecture.
